Safety_Information.general_Info: (S)-Methoprene, the active ingredient in DIACON® IGR, protects stored grains, agricultural commodities, seed, and animal feeds from damaging insects by interfering with the normal process of insect development. Unlike traditional pesticides, DIACON® IGR is not an adulticide, but its residual activity prevents the development of larvae into adults. When used according to the label directions, DIACON® IGR inhibits growth of larvae of these insects: almond moth, Indian meal moth, lesser grain borer, sawtoothed grain beetle, merchant grain beetle, red flour beetle, confused flour beetle, and other insect pests that are affected by Insect Growth Regulators (IGR’s). Treat existing insect populations with an adulticide, then apply DIACON® IGR for residual protection.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15-20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eyes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Immediately call a poison control center or doctor. Do not induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. Do not give ANY liquid to the person. Do not give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.if_On_Skin: Take off contaminated clothing. Rinse skin immediately with plenty of water for 15-20 minutes. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Contains petroleum distillates – vomiting may cause aspiration pneumonia.

Application_Info.application_Method: Apply in solution as a uniform coarse spray to the moving grain stream
